2 Project overview

CodeClan operates three campuses across three cities in Scotland:

  • Edinburgh
  • Glasgow
  • Inverness

Google Analytics Console is not user friendly and is restrictive in its ability to summarise CodeClan website traffic information.

This makes it difficult to measure the impact of specific marketing campaigns on web traffic or make comparisons over time and between CodeClan sites.

2.1 Project objective

  • Create a user-friendly product that draws upon and presents Google Analytics data

  • Focusing on the Central Belt, provide an overview and comparison of user sessions relating to the three CodeClan sites

  • Provide the ability to focus on specific time periods.


3 Product specification

Detail Information
Target audience: CodeClan Marketing Department
Specific Goals: Analyse and compare high-level website performance across CodeClan sites, based on geographic user location data
Design Problem: Limited or no ability to compare site performances in a single view

Overview of a single citys performance is not user-friendly

Difficult to measure non-digital campaign channels like radio or train station ads.
Project Timings: Tuesday 15th April - Approval of client brief and product specification

Wednesday 15th April 2020 - Product review and agreement of any changes

4 Product design - preliminary drafts

4.1 Dashboard concept

This is an early dashboard concept based upon our emphasis on readability with an intuitive layout. The final dashboard design will be a bit different and will incorporate a user-adjustable time scale.

4.2 Absolute user sessions chart

The presentation will change but this chart illustrates our ability to aggregate data from Google Analytics to draw more meaningful insight.

4.3 Relative user sessions chart

A different chart that compares user sessions as a proportion of overall Scottish web-traffic.


5 Additional information

5.1 Caveats

  • Website user location is based upon ISP location and not necessarily their physical geographic position
  • However, the data analysis still provides a broad overview of CodeClan website traffic and allows for relative comparison.
